  "final_text": "Two probes attached \u2014 the descriptor targets the L476RG, so I'll pin its probe serial and start from the project root (ELF autodiscovered):\nDebug session is up on the NUCLEO-L476RG:\n\n- **Target**: STM32L476RG, halted at attach (`target_state: halted`)\n- **ELF**: `BLINKY.elf` (autodiscovered from `stm32-project.jsonc`)\n- **gdbserver**: PID 149346 on port **61234**; gdb PID 149352\n- **Probe**: pinned to `066DFF485754727567021514` (the N6570-DK is also on the bench, so I selected explicitly)\n\nThe target is halted and ready. From here I can run one-shot recipes (`callstack`, `read-registers`, `read-peripheral GPIOA`, `snapshot`, \u2026) \u2014 just say what you want to inspect. If you'd rather the firmware keep running while attached, I can restart with `--no-halt`."
}